article.headline: UNC-Greensboro 70, Texas-Pan American 56
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Kyle Hines scored 19 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead North Carolina-Greensboro to a 70-56 win over Texas-Pan American Friday night in the opening round of the Price Cutter Classic. It was the 32nd career double-double for the senior forward. Greensboro (2-0) broke away from a 26-26 halftime score and took a 37-30 lead with 15 minutes to go. Texas-Pan American (2-1) went 6:25 without a field goal late in the second half before Dexter Shankle scored to get Greensboro within 52-43 with 5:45 left. Greensboro closed with an 18-13 run as UTPA shot 25 percent from the field in the second half. Mikko Koivisto scored 15 for Greensboro. Paul Stoll led Texas Pan-American with 16 points and Shankle finished with 12.
